import React from 'react';
import { Button, Container, Col, Form, Label, Input, FormGroup, } from 'reactstrap';

import "../App.css"

const SignUpForm = (props) => {
  return (
    <Container>
      <Form className="loginForm text-info">
      <FormGroup>
        <Label for="exampleName">First Name</Label>
        <Input type="Name" name="Name" id="exampleFirstName" placeholder="Insert Your First Name" />
      </FormGroup>
      <FormGroup>
        <Label for="exampleName">Last Name</Label>
        <Input type="Name" name="Name" id="exampleLastName" placeholder="Insert Your Last Name" />
      </FormGroup>
        <FormGroup>
          <Label for="exampleEmail">Email</Label>
          <Input type="email" name="email" id="exampleEmail" placeholder="Insert Your Email" />
        </FormGroup>
        <FormGroup>
          <Label for="examplePassword">Password</Label>
          <Input type="password" name="password" id="examplePassword" placeholder="Create Your Password" />
        </FormGroup>
        <FormGroup tag="fieldset" row>
          <legend className="col-form-label col-sm-2">Radio Buttons</legend>
          <Col sm={10}>
            <FormGroup check>
              <Label check>
                <Input type="radio" name="radio2" />{' '}
                Option one is this and thatâ€”be sure to include why it's great
              </Label>
            </FormGroup>
            <FormGroup check>
              <Label check>
                <Input type="radio" name="radio2" />{' '}
                Option two can be something else and selecting it will deselect option one
              </Label>
            </FormGroup>
            </Col>
        </FormGroup>
        <Button outline color="info" size="lg" block> Sign Up </Button>
      </Form>
    </Container>
   );
 }

export default SignUpForm;
